content.detailedDescription: I was driving home, headed west, at 430 am. to the wnw i saw a group of lightsthat resembled the complete structure of a large jet. it stayed in the same spotin the sky. when i got home 20 minutes later it was still there. i got mybinoculars, looked at the lights and saw a blue-white point withdistinct,individual yello-orange lights.Itwas there until 540 am.

I was in my 9th floor houston office facing north. spotted an object near thenorthwest corner of the 610 loop around houston. it was small and hard todetermine the altitude. it seemed to drift slowly to the south then to thesoutheast. the object appeared to be small and round. it seemed to wobble orspin. it flashed a fiery red light at an irregular interval. sometimes the lightwas quick and dim. other times it seemed to flare up. i thought it might be alarge balloon reflecting the setting sun in the west but the flashing had amechanical quality and seemed too red for reflected sunlight. as it slowlypassed over the building i lost sight of it and so left my office to godownstairs to see if i could catch it on the other side of the building. when icame outside and looked around it was gone. however at the same time i lookedsouth and saw a single military aircraft f-16 moving untypically fast from thedirection of ellington field and moving wnw. it seemed to be 3-5 miles to thesouth. the plane then went west and i think did a u-turn back toward the east. iwould note however that president bush is in town tonight for a fund raiser. thenews reported scrambeling an f-16 to intercept a private pilot in the same areabut no name or other details were given. it would be interesting to know if thiscould be confirmed with details. thats it. i dont know what it was. it was not aplane or helicopter. it seems like it could possibly have been a balloon of somekind but the flashing was weird - unless it has an irregular surface that wasspinning and possibly reflecting light from the sunset in the west. plausible -but i just cant say. it was certainly unusual enough to get and hold myattention. i took 3 digital photos of the small object which showed more detailthen i expected when enlarged. balloon you tell me. if you email me i will sendyou the photos.
content.summary: Flashing red sphere over houston with f-16 nearby

content.detailedDescription: I just pulled up to my condo, unloaded 1st bunch of groceries, out of the leftcorner of my eye, i saw this orange glow. i stopped unloaded grocieries to seewhat it was, due to the brightness of the object, it stood out in the sky. istood and watch it fly by almost directly above me coming from the n.E. andflying in a path to s.W. there was no sound what so ever as it passed. i watchit til it turned into a orange dot in the sky, ran in to get my binoculars, wentto my back yard, did see it thru the binoculars for about 15 to 20 minutesstaying in the same spot, moving slightly left, then a little right, it startedto pulsate, bright then dim, it got very bright , then it was gone. this eventwas about 845 pm to about 920. clear sky, full moon rising. the shape was aboomerang shape, but the orange glow was all around the shape itself, you couldsee some very slight features, the only thing that stands out besides the shapeand the glow, was a slight blue color in front, it was like you could somethingin front of this like a bubble around it pushing thru the air. i am very awareof aircraft and the shapes and colors lights etc airplanes civilianmilitarydo not light up like this

Going to get the mail, bright light blue sky with patchy clouds-high, always seeballoons, these seemed too large but ill always say they could be balloons,however, at this distance they would be as large as the front end of a largeplane.  they alternated black and silver as if the sun was reflecting as theywere rotating-as two balloons would do if spinning around eachother, one alittle lower than the other tied together.  there were two.  the one that washigher disappeared from my sight quickly, the other remained for a few minutesascending as a balloon would ascending a large imaginary spiral staircase. these were above and near nellis afb-i think-roughly above old henderson.  i wasstanding at home near the 215 and 15 roughly looking toward the intersection ofthe 215 and the 95.  it appeared to be a bit further than that---east, was ilooking  im one year new here from thousand oaks, ca.  p.S. my wife said sheheard on the news earlier that day there was going to be some fast flying jetsin the area.

At approx. 820 pm, march 3, 2004 las animas, colorado - southeastern colorado iheard a very load roar while watching t.V. in my front room. i went out side tohear what appeared to be a b1-b bomber at an altitude of 500 feet off theground. at this time the sound was extremly loud and much louder than a b1 lasanimas is located in  an moa - military operations area where b1s, fighter jets,b-52, f-117s train. i expected to see some type of airplane lights and strobesb1 strobes are usually a brilliant very fast strobe, all i did see was a largeoval white light, no stobes moving to the north. it appeared to be at a heightof a commerical jet, 20,000 plus feet. after watching the light move off to thenorth, i went inside and called the pueblo 80 miles west of las animas airporttower. they said that my area was out of their radar range and i needed to calldenver central. i did call denver and related to them the lightcraft and sound.The gentleman i spoke to said he would check and see if there was any militarytraffic or any aircraft in my area at that time. after several minutes he cameback on the phone and told me that it was not a b1 bomber or any military planeor commerical jet, but he did say that it was a classified aircraft on aclassified mission and that is all he could say about the event i have watched alot of aircraft over the years in this area and seen some strange aircraft, butthis one event was very unusual
content.summary: Classified military aircraft - ufo over las animas

I am 30 now and even though this happened a long time ago, i thought i shouldfinally report it to someone who might listen. the midwest is very conservativeand i dont think very many people believe. yet still today.I was only 9 or 10 years old and i was just getting home from being out playingwith friends and getting into all sorts of adventures, as i did virtually everyday and night growing up in the country. ive never been afraid of the dark andhad always had a high iq. at the time i knew nothing of the ufo phenomenon. i donot recall the exact time or date, but it was after dark and the weather waswarm. just as i reached my house i turned right to go up the stairs to the frontdoor and something bright caught my eye above the bluff. i turned to look at itand it was unbelievable it is still vivid in my mind. this thing was a glowingdiamond on its side it was less than 100 above the bluff and was flying movingfrom left to right but it was jerking up and down at the same time in anirregular motion. this bluff was maybe a mile away, and i had a clear line ofsight. there was no sound that i could hear. ive seen meteors break up, showers,ive always been fascinated with aircraft, etc. ...This thing had a definitecolor glowingneon yellow a definite shape a flattened diamond or diamond on itsside and a definite path in the sky it skimmed the tree tops as it flew fromleft to right and jerked up and down in a irregular path. these are not myinterpretations, this is exactly what i saw.I was so scared that this thing was going to see me i panicked and ran insideand told my mother. i do not think she saw it when she looked out the window.I do not remember what i was doing before or what happened afterward.P.S. i also have a few other stories when i was in high school i had what ibelieve was a rod fly about 10 feet in front of me when i was walking up my longdriveway after getting home from school. this was a different house than the ufosighting same county - about 10 miles away. i did not know what rods even wereuntil about 3 years ago. both the ufo and this rod were the only 2 things thatscared me so bad as a kid that i remembered it still todaythis rod flew on a horizontal path out if the tree line across the road just infront of me and into the tree line on the other side. at first i just thought itwas a leaf because it was a rusty color. but it did not fall, it flew withoutdropping in elevation and flew about 20-30 feet before it just vanished intothin air just inside the tree line. i

022604 tonight at approx 730pm eastern time i observed two small objects approx100 feet above a wooded area in the town i live. i was driving home from gettinggas and observed the two objects glowing red, green, and white they werehovering and very slowly heading in a westward direction. at first i thoughtthey might be helicopters or small planes. i lost sight of them for a couple ofseconds behind some trees and when i was able to see again only one of them wasthere. i pulled off onto a side road and turned the vehicle off and rolled downmy window. at this time and for the duration of the sighting no sound wasapparent. i watched for about a minute. i looked around to see if there were anymore and did not see any. when i looked back the second object had reappeared. iobserved both objects hovering for about five more minutes. suddenly the firstobject dissapeared followed a couple of seconds later by the second. i waitedfor about five more minutes and they did not reappear. they seemed to behovering like fireflys as best as i can describe it. they would go slowly up anddown and side to side in no set pattern. i did not observe any sudden movementsor anything else.I live in nw pennsylvania in a very rural area about a mile south of lake erie.I did a little research and found similar objects being seen in this areabefore. i am about 30 miles east of the perry nuclear power plant and objects ofthis or similar nature have been observed there since the 80s.On a side note, about a week ago i saw what appeared to me to be one of thosesmall airplanes they were using in iraq. the un piloted white ones. i onlycaught a glimpse of it but what i did notice was that it was white with novisable markings. it was also flying very low in an area about a half mile fromthe 2 objects i saw today.
content.summary: 2 objects glowing red green and white  nw pennsyl

content.detailedDescription: I was driving north from girdwood to anchorage when i noticed a glowing ballfloating over the water in the inlet.  i thought that it may have been ahelicopter spotlight, but it was very foggy and it was much lighter and adifferent color.  it only followed at the same speed as my vehicle.  i wasmostly amazed at what i was seeing.  it was something that i had never seenbefore.  it glowed a yellowish white color that illuminated the surroundings ofmy vehicle.  i believe the fog also enhanced the effect.  i then felt as if ihad fallen asleep, but i was a few miles down the road from where i was anddriving a lot slower than before.  when i looked at ocean to see the object, ithad dissappeared.  i never told anyone until a couple of years ago.  i neverfelt compelled to share my experience, but recently have had very strongthoughts about the experience.  the other strange thing is a loss of time duringthe sighting.  it seemed that i had been sleeping and had woken up 20 minuteslater.  i know i did not fall asleep, but the time somehow went by.  hope thishelps.  thanks.

content.detailedDescription: I had just parked in my employment parking lot and a co-worker arrived at thesame time.  i noticed the object because a large, black crow sitting atop alight pole started crowing really loud.  i was waiting for my co-worker to exithis vehicle so we could walk in together, and i heard the crow and thought itodd that it would be there making such a loud noise. i had never noticed a crowin the parking lot before so it kind of stood out.  i saw the crow, felt somehowdisconnected to my surroundings, as though i were experiencing a dream in someway.  when the co-worker came up alongside me, i pointed the crow out to him andmade a comment about how strange it seemed.  thats when i first noticed theobject in the sky.  my first thought was a large mylar balloon drifting in thewind. but the shape of the object was so odd that i couldnt quite fathom justwhat type of mylar balloon it could be.  i felt a moment of quiet come over meas the thought struck that i may be seeing something that is different thananything id ever seen before. the object moved slowly, as though drifting on thewind, so we watched it for some time, maybe five minutes, discussing what it maybe.  my friend commented that it was certainly strange, but that it must have agood explanation, even though he couldnt think of one himself.  he refuses tobelieve that it could have been anything other than of terresterial origin, ashe is not a believer in ufos i was simply stunned to be seeing this object.  iwanted to chase it to see where it went, but i had to got to work so once theobject was out of sight, we left.Im not good with distance, but the object seemed to be roughly 10-15 in size. it was silver in color though not really as reflective as a true silver colormay be.  possibly lead colored, would be a better description.  its appearencewas that of a bundle of cylinders bunched together.  maybe as many as 8, butcertainly no less than six.  its appearence gave the impression of looking likea six pack of coors light beer, only without the lettering on the cans and,obviously, much larger. there were no windows or doors or lights that i couldsee, only the six to eight lead colored cylinders moving to the northwest.  theobject moved from a generally southern to northwestern direction, moving slowlybut steady.
content.summary: Observed silvery, unrecognized obect in the sky

Late summer of 2003, one afternoon, my wife and i were traveling east onfranconia springfield parkway, springfield, va. just pass the springfield metrosubway station and at about 1100 oclock position, my wife noticed two strangecloud-like formations in the sky. she pointed these objects out to me and theywere very noticeable, being that the sky was rather clear and blue. at first ithought they were hot air balloons but then i noticed that they were like vaporclouds, and somewhat thick in consistency since both were casting a shadow. theshape of these ufos were identical to each other, their tops were circular inshape, as domes, and both had trails at their base, similar to tentacles from ajellyfish. they did not seem to move from their positions, static as theyfloated above. i do recall thinking that they may have been the results of anaircraft aerial backfires if there is such a thing spewing vaporous balls ofsmoky, oily residue. no sounds were emitted.More info at this sitehttpmembers.Aol.Comfacadefxpage4.Html
content.summary: Two jellyfish ufos over skies of sprinfield, va

content.detailedDescription: My daughter and i were leaving the pre-investiture celebration for the newbishop coajutor for the dioceses of west texas when we noticed a very brightstar low on the horizon.  upon closer inspection the object appeared to havelights and was circular in shape.  the object stayed still and we check to seeif it was a light on a large crane or on top of a building, it was not.  wedecided to find some witnesses to the event and went back towards sunsetstation.  we had to walk behind a two story building to get to where the peoplewere and when we came out from behind the building it was gone.  we then walkedback towards our car, our original destination, and the object seemed to comeout from a cloud and was in the same spot it originally was.  we continued tolook at the object for about a minute, and then it disappeared into the cloud. then proceeded down 281 north to get some dinner, when we came to the quarrymall, in olmos basin, we looked to the west and say the same object again, justhovering.  we then became concerned and exited to loop 410 and proceeded tobetos comida latina restaurant and tolled the night manager, who is anaquaintance what were had seen.  when we went home we tried not to look in thesky, because we didnt want to see the object again.

On october 12, 1987, at my fiances house in somerville, in, at approximately11:45 p.M., my fiance darren and i were in bed, in the middle of intercourse, when we both apparently blacked out at the exact same time.  the following morning, we were awakened by my mother, who was knocking on the screen door.  it was raining outside, and the main entry door was unlocked and wide open. the lights inside the house were all on.  we had locked the doors and shut off all of the lights before going to bed the night before.  my mother said she heard metal clanging sounds when she came to the door. we had new stove pipe lying on the living room floor, as we were preparing to install a new furnace.  she also heard what sounded to her like an old man coughing in a deep tone. when we finally came to, we were both naked and lying in two different directions on the bed. both of us had tremendous headaches and a feeling that something strange had happened to us, but did not talk about it.  for the next two days, when we each tried to think about what had happened, our minds couldn't focus on the event. after some time had passed, we both realized that we could both remember right up to the exact moment that we both blacked out it had happened right in the middle of sex, and we had blacked out at the exact same time. two months later, i found out i was pregnant, and would have conceived at around this same date. also, i was on birth control pills at the time. a few months later, in feb. 1988, we were asleep when i was awakened at 2:48 am, by a small, gray, wrinkled-looking being. he had large eyes, no nose, and just a slit where his mouth should've been. he was standing about four feet from the bed, just staring at me.  he had a solid, dark-colored outfit on - it looked like a one-piece jumpsuit.  i tried to wake darren, but was unable to move. i tried to scream for him, but was only able to make a wimpering sound.  at that time, darren rolled over towards me, and the being just faded out of existence. i told darren what i had seen, and we finally got back to sleep. at exactly 4:48am 2 hours later, i was again awakened by the same small, gray being.  i laid there looking at him for probably 3-4 minutes
